<h2>Box Model, a.k.a. spacing</h2>

<div class="annotated-code">
  <pre class="prettyprint linenums lang-css">
.spaced {
	width: 200px;
	height: 100px;
	padding: 10px 5px;
	border: 5px solid black;
	margin: 10px 5px;
}
</pre>
  <div class="annotation" data-line="4">
    Padding: Refers to spacing between the content and the border
  </div>
  <div class="annotation" data-line="5">
    Border: Size of the border
  </div>
  <div class="annotation" data-line="6">
    Margin: Refers to spacing between the next element and the border.
  </div>
</div>

<img src="/images/boxmodel.png" />


<div class="panel panel-info">
  <div class="panel-heading">
    <h3 class="panel-title">Specifying different spaces for different sides</h3>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-body">
    <p>To select different sizes for different sides, you simply specify the pixel sizes in clockwise order starting from top.  (e.g. padding: 1px 2px 3px 4px means 1px padding at the top, 2px on the right, 3px on the bottom, etc.).  A short hand for saying 10px at top and bottom and 5px for left and right is just to specify 2 values, e.g. padding: 10px 5px.</p>
  </div>
</div>

