<h2>Floats</h2>

<p>Floats are useful for arranging multiple divs next to each other horizontally. (for example, if I have multiple cards I want to show side-by-side)</p>

<pre class="prettyprint lang-css">
float: left;
float: right;
clear: both;
</pre>

<div class="annotated-code">
  <pre class="prettyprint linenums lang-css">
float: left;
float: right;
clear: both;
</pre>
  <div class="annotation" data-line="1">
    Effectively lifts the div and floats it to the left such that the div following it can come up to its right.
  </div>
  <div class="annotation" data-line="3">
    Border: Size of the border
  </div>
  <div class="annotation" data-line="6">
    This is an important property that makes sure that any floating divs before it will stay above it.
  </div>
</div>

